data.title: Imre Kertesz, Holocaust Survivor and Nobel Laureate, Dies at 86
data.meta_description: Kertesz Won the 2002 Nobel Literature Prize for Works the Judges Said Portrayed the Nazi Death Camps as "The Ultimate Truth" About How Low Human Beings Could Fall.
